2. cs.COMM (Networking and Internet Architecture) is also likely as the paper deals with communication channels and their capacity bounds. 
3. cs.SI (Signal Processing) is another possible sub-category as the paper deals with bandlimited channels and pulse shaping, which are important topics in signal processing. 
4. cs.MM (Multimedia) is a possible sub-category as the paper deals with peak power constraints, which are relevant in multimedia applications such as audio and video compression. 
5. cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture) is another possible sub-category as the paper deals with capacity bounds for communication channels, which is a topic relevant to networking and internet architecture.
